Male genitalia. Pygofer in lateral view with caudoventral lobe long, broad, narrowed distally, ventral margin folded near middle, caudodorsal margin with paired processes, bent subapically (
Fig. 64
). Segment X ventral processes slender, exceeding margin of pygofer, apex hooked ventrad in lateral view (
Fig. 64
). Subgenital plate long and narrow, segmented subbasally, marginal setae fine long or short (
Fig. 66
). Dorsal connective broad Ushaped, stem absent, rami long, attaching to base of segment X ventral processes by membrane (
Fig. 65
). Aedeagus in dorsal view symmetrical, short, about 1 / 3 as long as paraphysis, broad basally, gradually narrowed apically (
Figs. 67, 68
); paraphysis in dorsal view asymmetrical, broad throughout, narrowest near midlength, right margin with serrate fold from base to middle, opposite side expanded distally with short, retrorse spine subapically at broadest point, apex with hooked spine, in lateral view X-shaped, both spines twisted dorsally, right margin expanded subbasally and narrowed apically, outer margin narrowed basally and expanded distally (
Figs. 67, 68
). Style long, exceeding the midlength of paraphysis, base broad, tapered to apex, subbase twisted (
Figs. 67, 69
).

Female genitalia. Abdominal sternite VII in ventral view with base broad, narrowed distally, anterior margin nearly straight, posterior margin with shallow emargination medially, lateral margins convex (
Fig. 74
). Internal sternite VIII completely membranous. Pygofer in lateral view, moderately produced posteriorly, dorsoposterior margin obliquely truncate, with macrosetae extending to ventral margin in posterior half (
Fig. 75
). Valvifer I in lateral view, broad, posterodorsal margin with a small lobe (
Fig. 76
). Valvifer II length-width ratio 3 : 1 , in lateral view, nearly fusiform, with small group of clustered setae above articulation point, articulation point located on submedian (
Fig. 77
). Valvulae I long, in lateral view curved, medial 1 / 2 narrowed, distal 1 / 4 broadened and gradually narrowed towards acute apex (
Fig. 78
), with horizontally nephroid sculptured sclerotized area on the basal half of shaft ventrally (
Fig. 79
), and with obliquely striated sclerotized area on dorsal margin 1 / 4 and on ventral margin near apex (
Fig. 80
). Valvulae II long, basal 3 / 4 with membrane joining two sides, distal 1 / 4 detached and narrowed gradually to tip, shaft bearing 18 or 20 teeth over posterior 1 / 4 of each blade, and one shared tooth at apex of joint area, teeth rounded, widely spaced, apicoventral margin without teeth, dorsal margin of blade without secondary denticles, ducts well delimited, extending to teeth and towards apical blade portion in lateral and dorsal views (
Figs. 81–83
). Valvulae III in lateral view, expanded at apical half, apex obtuse, surface with fine setae mostly distributed on apical portion and extending anteriorly along ventral margin of apical half (
Fig. 84
).
